 
  ################# Execution of a Java Program #####################
  Before jumping into the internals of Java, let’s understand how a Java source file 
is executed.

* We write the Java source code in JavaFirstProgram.
Java file using an editor or IDE (integrated development environment) 
e.g. Eclipse or IntelliJ Idea.
* Program has to be compiled into bytecode. Java compiler (javac) compiles 
the source-code to JavaFirstProgram.class file.
* This class file can be executed in any platform/OS by JVM (Java virtual machine).
* JVM translates bytecode into native machine code which machines can execute.
  
  
  
